The paper deals with the development of virtual reality and multimedia content, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The establishment of a novel omnidirectional image dataset and benchmarking of stitching models involve graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects. Additionally, the use of evaluation metrics for image quality assessment suggests a possible connection to multimedia systems and applications (cs.MMSE).
